{% endfor %}
ENVIRONMENT CONTINUITY (use these locked-in environment descriptions for any scene set in the named locale):
{% for env, desc in bible.environment_continuity.items() %}- {{ env }}: {{ desc }}
{% endfor %}
STORY BIBLE LEAD INSTRUCTIONS (binding):
- Lead each visual_prompt with the scene's hero_shot from the bible.
- Name EVERY character in visible_characters explicitly by name (use the bible's character_continuity description for each).
- Include EVERY prop in props_visible by name with a strong visual modifier ("brass bells dangling from the cap tip" beats "bell-cap").
- The light_source must appear in the visual_prompt as the primary lit anchor.
- brightness_floor is binding: low = chiaroscuro permitted (a face lit, the rest dark); medium = a discernible foreground + a partly-visible environment; high = a fully-lit composition. NEVER write a prompt that bans every light source.
- The negative_prompt MUST NOT exclude any of: candle, torch, flame, lantern, lamp, fire, "light source" (case insensitive, all word stems — "lamps", "lamplight", "firelight" all count). The rewriter's previous failure mode was banning the lit anchors Flux needs; the post-condition regex rejects any of these tokens in negative_prompt regardless of qualifier ("no streetlamps" still trips the gate). If you need to forbid a related concept, phrase it without these stems (e.g. "bright daylight" instead of "no overhead lamp glow").
{% endif %}

CONVENTIONS

Visual prompts target Flux 1.0 Dev at 9:16 portrait aspect ratio (768x1344).

Each prompt MUST open with one of these camera-framing tokens (no exceptions):
- "extreme close-up", "close-up", "medium shot", "medium-wide shot", "wide shot",
  "over-the-shoulder shot", "low-angle shot", "high-angle shot"

Each prompt MUST state the main subject's pose in active verb form:
- GOOD: "kneeling, holding a candle"
- GOOD: "chained to a stone wall"
- GOOD: "bricking up a niche with a trowel"
- BAD:  "torchlit man at wall" (no active verb; vague pose)
- BAD:  "in the catacombs" (no subject pose at all)

Each prompt MUST state spatial layout when 2+ subjects are present:
- GOOD: "Foreground: Montresor in dark cloak. Background: Fortunato in motley leaning against the wall."
- BAD:  "two men in the catacombs"

Each prompt MUST state the dominant lighting source and direction in lit-pixel
terms (S6.4 darkness-density caps remain load-bearing):
- GOOD: "amber torchlight from upper-left catching their faces and the wet stone wall"
- BAD:  "low-key chiaroscuro lighting" (atmospheric-only; no lit pixels named)

End with at most ONE styling clause:
- "painterly cinematography, dim mood" -- yes
- "oil painting quality, fine film grain, Caravaggio palette, deep crimson highlights" -- no

Track styling is appended automatically as a tail tag: [atmospheric horror style].
Do NOT expand this tag in the prompt body.

Output exactly one entry per scene; preserve the input scene index.

NEW REQUIRED FIELDS PER SCENE (in addition to visual_prompt + negative_prompt):
- composition_notes: 1-2 sentence stage direction in plain prose. Example:
  "Medium shot. Two men face each other across a vault arch. Foreground:
   Montresor in dark cloak holding a torch. Background: Fortunato in jester
   motley, leaning against the wall."
  Used downstream by the pose+depth map stage; does NOT go directly to Flux.
- character_refs: list of recurring character names appearing in this scene.
  Use names from the TRACK CHARACTERS section below. Empty list if no named
  recurring character is in this scene.

DARKNESS DENSITY CAPS (atmospheric horror -- Flux fades to black on
over-loaded dark prompts; mean RGB hits 0-3 and the keyframe is unviewable):
- At most one explicit darkness cue per clause. Stacked dark / shadow /
  blackness / chiaroscuro signals collapse the rendered image.
- Describe subjects in LIT terms, not absent terms. Tell Flux which
  PIXELS are bright -- name a lit edge, a lit surface, and a lit
  material per scene where possible. "Candlelight catching the bridge
  of the nose and the rim of the goblet" beats "face turned toward a
  candle." "Amber-lit face" beats "half-lit, half lost in shadow."
- Atmosphere belongs to adjectives, not to the subject. "Man in candlelit
  study" -- yes. "Candlelit study at night, mostly black, with a man
  somewhere inside" -- no.
- Negative prompts MUST NOT fight the scene's own light source. Forbidden:
  "multiple light sources" when the prompt needs candlelight to reach the
  subject. (Daylight remains a valid negative cue -- "bright daylight"
  excludes a scene type, not a brightness floor.)

LENGTH BUDGET (S8.C, binding -- Flux drops directives past ~600 chars; the
S8.B verify run produced 1000-1700-char visual_prompts and Flux rendered
roughly half of each, scoring 4-5/10 in human eye-check):
- visual_prompt: 350-600 characters total. Hard cap 700. Count whitespace.
- negative_prompt: 350-500 characters total. Hard cap 600.
- Front-load priority order: [camera] [period anchor] [pose+subject]
  [lit anchor] [props x2] [single styling tail].
- Do NOT inline the FULL bible character_continuity description into every
  scene. Use the bible's Face/Costume/Posture signatures as a SOURCE; emit
  a CONDENSED 8-15-word scene-specific reference per visible character
  (e.g. "Montresor in black wool cloak, gaunt face, neat dark goatee" --
  not the full 30-word continuity description). Cross-scene face identity
  is locked downstream by IP-Adapter; the visual_prompt only needs enough
  to anchor Flux's render of THIS scene.
{% if period is defined and period %}
PERIOD ANCHORING (S8.C, binding -- without this Flux drifts to generic
"moody horror" or modern dress regardless of bible content):
- The period "{{ period }}" MUST appear in every visual_prompt, immediately
  AFTER the camera-framing token, in 5-8 words. Verbatim or near-verbatim.
- Format: "<camera-token>, {{ period }}, <subject> <pose>, <lit anchor>, ..."
- The single styling tail clause SHOULD lean on the period_styling cue
  ("{{ period_styling }}") -- you may shorten or pair it with one mood
  word (e.g. "oil-painting cinematography, dim mood") but the era cue
  must remain detectable in the tail.
- Do NOT spell out individual artist names in the prompt body unless the
  bible's hero_shot or color_anchors explicitly invokes them.
{% endif %}
PROP REPETITION (S8.C, binding for small or load-bearing props -- single
mentions get dropped by Flux):
- Every prop in the scene's bible.props_visible list MUST appear TWICE in
  the visual_prompt with DIFFERENT modifiers (not the same noun-adjective
  pair repeated). The second mention can ride on the lit-anchor or
  composition clause.
- GOOD: "iron mason's trowel held flat across his gloved palm... the
  worn-handled blade catching the torchlight"
- BAD:  "the trowel" + "the trowel" (same noun, no modifier variation)
- Exempt: a prop the lighting clause already names (e.g. the torch in
  "amber torchlight from upper-right") only needs ONE explicit prop
  mention beyond the lighting clause.

MOOD WORDS DON'T RENDER -- TRANSLATE TO PIXEL CUES (S8.C, binding):
- The bible's emotional_energy field is an authoring guide, not a Flux
  directive. Bare mood adjectives ("ominous", "tense", "decadent",
  "predatory", "sinister", "patient hatred", "dread") render as nothing
  or as garbled overlay text.
- Every mood adjective in the visual_prompt MUST be paired with a 2-4
  word PIXEL cue describing what light, body, or material renders the
  mood. Examples:
  - "ominous"   -> "deep shadows pooling in the corners"
  - "tense"     -> "white knuckles on the goblet, jaw clenched"
  - "predatory" -> "thin smile, eyes flat and unblinking"
  - "patient"   -> "still hands, no body motion, set jaw"
  - "decadent"  -> "rich brocade fabric, gold thread embroidery"
  - "sinister"  -> "lips curled in a half-smile, eyes lit from below"
  - "dread"     -> "wide eyes, opened mouth, frozen mid-action"
- Bare mood adjectives without a paired pixel cue are forbidden.

NEGATIVE PROMPT REQUIREMENTS (S8.C, binding -- 350-500 chars total):
Every negative_prompt MUST include items from each of these classes:
- Modernity bans: at least three of {modern clothing, contemporary,
  21st century, modern hair, plastic, polyester, polished smooth surfaces,
  modern eyewear, sneakers, jeans}
- Quality bans: at least three of {smooth airbrushed skin, oversaturated
  HDR, anime, cartoon, illustration, digital art look, photoshop look}
- Lighting bans (when scene is candlelit/torchlit): at least two of
  {full face illumination, flat overhead lighting, ring light look,
  daylight studio, fluorescent}
- AI artifact bans: at least one of {extra fingers, mangled hands,
  asymmetric eyes, blurry face}
Combine those with at most 4 scene-specific exclusions (e.g. "Fortunato
smiling broadly", "trowel out of frame"). The exposure-guardrail bans
(no candle/torch/flame/lantern/lamp/fire/light source word stems) STILL
APPLY -- those are checked by the post-condition regex.

